### Basic usage of ResponsiveContainer for a responsive chart

Source: https://github.com/recharts/recharts/blob/main/storybook/stories/API/ResponsiveContainer.mdx

This JSX snippet demonstrates how to wrap a Recharts chart component, such as `LineChart`, within a `ResponsiveContainer` to make it adapt to its parent's dimensions. It sets the width to fill 100% of the parent and a fixed height of 400px, allowing the child chart to automatically receive the calculated dimensions after client-side rendering.

```jsx
<ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height={400}>
  <LineChart {...args}>
    <Line dataKey="uv" />
  </LineChart>
</ResponsiveContainer>
```

